  "prompt": "How do you tie a tie?",
  "response": "Tying a tie is a classic skill that can add a touch of elegance to your outfit. Here's a step-by-step guide to tying the most common knot, the **Four-in-Hand**:\n\n### **Steps to Tie a Four-in-Hand Knot:**\n1. **Start Position:** Drape the tie around your neck with the wide end on your right side and the narrow end on your left. The wide end should hang about 12 inches lower than the narrow end.\n  \n2. **Cross the Ends:** Cross the wide end over the narrow end.\n\n3. **Loop Around:** Bring the wide end under the narrow end and then up to the right.\n\n4. **Pull Through the Loop:** Bring the wide end down through the loop around your neck.\n\n5. **Tighten:** Hold the narrow end and pull the wide end gently to tighten the knot. Slide the knot up to your collar.\n\n### **Tips:**\n- Adjust the length so the tip of the wide end touches the top of your belt buckle.\n- Make sure the knot is snug but not too tight.\n- Practice a few times to get it right!\n\nIf you'd like to learn other knots like the **Windsor** or **Half-Windsor**, let me know!",
